Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.71,0:01:37.01,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The age and size of the cosmos{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.04,0:01:40.15,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}are written in light.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.18,0:01:45.02,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The nature of beauty and{\i}\N{\i1}the substance of the stars,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.05,0:01:48.42,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the laws of space and time...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.46,0:01:51.42,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}they were there all along,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.46,0:01:53.46,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but we never saw them...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.49,0:01:57.33,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}until we devised{\i}\N{\i1}a more powerful way of seeing.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.36,0:02:01.03,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The story of this awakening{\i}\N{\i1}has many beginnings{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.07,0:02:03.20,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and no ending.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.24,0:02:06.44,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Its heroes come from many times{\i}\N{\i1}and places--{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.47,0:02:09.28,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}an Ancient Chinese philosopher,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.31,0:02:12.98,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}a wizard who amazed the caliphs{\i}\N{\i1}of 11th-century Iraq,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.01,0:02:17.88,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}a poor German orphan enslaved{\i}\N{\i1}to a harsh master.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.92,0:02:20.35,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Each one brought us{\i}\N{\i1}a little closer{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.39,0:02:24.59,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to unlocking the secrets{\i}\N{\i1}hidden in light.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.23,0:02:30.66,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Most of their names{\i}\N{\i1}are forever lost to us,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.70,0:02:35.20,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but somewhere, long ago,{\i}\N{\i1}someone glanced up{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.24,0:02:39.61,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to see light perform{\i}\N{\i1}one of its magic tricks.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.93,0:03:01.93,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Who knows?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.96,0:03:03.73,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Maybe that quirk of light{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.76,0:03:05.90,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}inspired the very first artist.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.14,0:03:21.18,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Where did all this come from?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.21,0:03:24.78,English1,,0,0,0,,How did we evolve\Nfrom small wandering bands
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.82,0:03:26.95,English1,,0,0,0,,of hunters and gatherers living\Nbeneath the stars
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.99,0:03:30.76,English1,,0,0,0,,to become the builders\Nof a global civilization?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.79,0:03:34.23,English1,,0,0,0,,How did we get from there\Nto here?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.26,0:03:36.06,English1,,0,0,0,,There's no one answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.10,0:03:38.76,English1,,0,0,0,,Climate change,\Nthe domestication of fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.80,0:03:43.30,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the invention of tools,{\i}\N{\i1}language, agriculture{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.34,0:03:46.61,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}all played a role.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.64,0:03:49.27,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Maybe there was{\i}\N{\i1}something else, too.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.31,0:03:52.44,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In China,{\i}\N{\i1}more than 2,000 years ago,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.48,0:03:55.65,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}a philosopher named Mo Tze{\i}\N{\i1}is said to have observed{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.68,0:03:58.05,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}that light could be made{\i}\N{\i1}to paint a picture{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.08,0:04:00.32,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}inside a locked treasure room.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.35,0:04:05.79,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This was the description{\i}\N{\i1}of the first camera...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.83,0:04:07.93,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the camera obscura,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.96,0:04:10.33,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the prototype of all{\i}\N{\i1}image-forming cameras,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.36,0:04:13.63,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}including the one that's{\i}\N{\i1}bringing you this picture.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.67,0:04:16.27,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Taking advantage of this funny{\i}\N{\i1}thing that light does{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.30,0:04:21.27,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}resulted in what could be{\i}\N{\i1}called the first movie.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.31,0:04:27.08,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Mo Tze, master of light, worked{\i}\N{\i1}against all forms of darkness.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.11,0:04:28.85,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A military genius{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.88,0:04:32.02,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}who only used his talents{\i}\N{\i1}to prevent violence,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.05,0:04:34.02,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}he was legendary for traveling{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.05,0:04:36.16,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}among the kingdoms{\i}\N{\i1}of the warring states,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.19,0:04:37.92,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}employing ingenious strategies{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.96,0:04:39.99,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to talk kings out{\i}\N{\i1}of going to war.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.03,0:04:43.60,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He was one of the first{\i}\N{\i1}to dream of universal love{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.63,0:04:46.70,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and an end to poverty{\i}\N{\i1}and other forms of inequality;{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.73,0:04:50.67,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}of government for the people...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.70,0:04:53.14,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and to argue against{\i}\N{\i1}blind obedience{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.17,0:04:54.54,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to ritual and authority.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.57,0:04:56.14,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In his writings, you can find{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.18,0:04:59.88,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}early stirrings{\i}\N{\i1}of the scientific approach.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.91,0:05:02.85,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}By Mo Tze's time, the Chinese{\i}\N{\i1}had already been recording{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.88,0:05:06.22,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}their thoughts in books{\i}\N{\i1}for at least a thousand years.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.25,0:05:09.19,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Still, our knowledge of him{\i}\N{\i1}is only fragmentary.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.22,0:05:11.66,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It consists largely{\i}\N{\i1}of the collection of essays{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.69,0:05:13.36,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}attributed to him{\i}\N{\i1}and his disciples.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.39,0:05:16.53,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In one of them,{\i}\N{\i1}entitled "Against Fate,"{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.56,0:05:19.67,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}a three-pronged test{\i}\N{\i1}for every doctrine is proposed.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.70,0:05:22.20,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Question its basis--{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.24,0:05:23.90,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}ask if it can be verified{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.94,0:05:26.47,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}by the sights and senses{\i}\N{\i1}of common people--{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.51,0:05:28.24,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}ask how it is to be applied{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.27,0:05:30.61,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and if it will benefit{\i}\N{\i1}the greatest number.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.05,0:05:37.52,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Mo Tze was extremely popular,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.55,0:05:39.85,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but a few hundred years{\i}\N{\i1}after his death,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.89,0:05:42.82,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Qin Shi Huang,{\i}\N{\i1}the first emperor,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.86,0:05:45.89,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and unifier of China,{\i}\N{\i1}took power.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.93,0:05:48.49,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He took a continent{\i}\N{\i1}and turned it into a nation{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.53,0:05:51.93,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}that now bears his name... China.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.97,0:05:59.44,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Most of us know Emperor Qin{\i}\N{\i1}for the army of 7,000{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.47,0:06:02.78,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}terra cotta warriors{\i}\N{\i1}that guard his tomb.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.64,0:06:07.58,English1,,0,0,0,,In Emperor Qin's drive
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.61,0:06:10.22,English1,,0,0,0,,to consolidate\Nhis far-flung empire,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.25,0:06:11.92,English1,,0,0,0,,he took drastic measures
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.95,0:06:14.42,English1,,0,0,0,,to standardize everything\Nwithin it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.45,0:06:17.39,English1,,0,0,0,,This included mandating\Na single coinage,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.42,0:06:19.96,English1,,0,0,0,,making uniform all weights\Nand measures,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.99,0:06:23.80,English1,,0,0,0,,the widths of carts and roads,\Nas well as the precise way
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.83,0:06:26.03,English1,,0,0,0,,the Chinese language was\Nto be written,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.07,0:06:31.10,English1,,0,0,0,,including what you were\Nallowed to write and think.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.14,0:06:33.91,English1,,0,0,0,,Emperor Qin's philosophy--\Nthe only one permitted--
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.94,0:06:35.54,English1,,0,0,0,,was called "legalism,"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.58,0:06:38.14,English1,,0,0,0,,which is just what\Nit sounded like,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.18,0:06:41.58,English1,,0,0,0,,do as the law says... or else.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.02,0:06:44.65,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's a philosophy that's{\i}\N{\i1}not highly conducive{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.68,0:06:46.69,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to questioning authority.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.76,0:06:54.56,English1,,0,0,0,,...that all the books of\Nthe hundred schools of thought
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.59,0:06:56.23,English1,,0,0,0,,shall be be burned,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.26,0:06:59.67,English1,,0,0,0,,that anyone who uses history\Nto criticize the present
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.70,0:07:01.97,English1,,0,0,0,,shall have his family executed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.00,0:07:06.11,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The works of{\i}\N{\i1}MoTze and Confucius{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.14,0:07:08.34,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and other philosophers{\i}\N{\i1}were destroyed{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.38,0:07:10.34,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}in the world's first{\i}\N{\i1}book burning.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.38,0:07:12.95,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Hundreds of scholars{\i}\N{\i1}bravely resisted{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.98,0:07:15.68,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}by trying to preserve{\i}\N{\i1}the forbidden books.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.72,0:07:18.32,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They were buried alive{\i}\N{\i1}in the capitol.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.05,0:07:23.86,English1,,0,0,0,,Science needs the light\Nof free expression to flourish.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.89,0:07:27.26,English1,,0,0,0,,It depends on the fearless\Nquestioning of authority,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.29,0:07:29.86,English1,,0,0,0,,the open exchange of ideas.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.90,0:07:33.60,English1,,0,0,0,,Sparks of curiosity\Nin the writings of Mo Tze
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.63,0:07:37.37,English1,,0,0,0,,and his disciples were\Neffectively stomped out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.40,0:07:42.01,English1,,0,0,0,,It would be another thousand\Nyears before the next movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.91,0:07:46.15,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Luckily, our Ship{\i}\N{\i1}of the Imagination{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.18,0:07:50.18,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}can take us anywhere{\i}\N{\i1}in space... and time.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.85,0:08:00.52,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The ancient Chinese{\i}\N{\i1}and Greeks observed{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.55,0:08:02.19,English1,,0,0,0,,that light could be made
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.22,0:08:05.02,English1,,0,0,0,,to do wonderful things--\Nbut no one asked that question
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.06,0:08:10.33,English1,,0,0,0,,favored by small children\Nand geniuses alike. Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.36,0:08:13.40,English1,,0,0,0,,Until a thousand years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.50,0:08:20.84,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In the city of Basra, Iraq,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.87,0:08:22.84,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}there lived{\i}\N{\i1}another master of light.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.87,0:08:28.21,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Ibn al-Hazen had a passionate{\i}\N{\i1}desire to understand nature.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.25,0:08:30.35,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He questioned everything,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.38,0:08:34.32,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}especially those things that{\i}\N{\i1}everyone else took for granted.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.25,0:08:39.46,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"How do we see?" he asked.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.49,0:08:41.86,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Some of the great authorities{\i}\N{\i1}who came before him{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.89,0:08:45.46,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}had taught that rays come out{\i}\N{\i1}of our eyes and travel{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.50,0:08:49.83,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to the objects we see{\i}\N{\i1}before returning to our eyes.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.87,0:08:53.74,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But al-Hazen reasoned that{\i}\N{\i1}the stars were too far distant{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.77,0:08:56.34,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}for something in our eyes{\i}\N{\i1}to travel all the way to them{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.37,0:08:59.01,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and back in the blink{\i}\N{\i1}of an eye.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.04,0:09:02.68,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Excellent reasoning,{\i}\N{\i1}but al-Hazen didn't stop there.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.71,0:09:06.98,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He searched for ways to compel{\i}\N{\i1}nature to divulge her secrets.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.02,0:09:10.32,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}His culture was open{\i}\N{\i1}to new ideas and questioning.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.36,0:09:12.82,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It was the golden age{\i}\N{\i1}of science{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.86,0:09:15.06,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}in the Islamic world.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.09,0:09:18.53,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}One that stretched from Cordoba{\i}\N{\i1}in Spain{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.56,0:09:22.17,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}all the way to Samarkand{\i}\N{\i1}in Central Asia.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.20,0:09:25.20,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Christian and Jewish scholars{\i}\N{\i1}were honored guests{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.24,0:09:27.94,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}at the research institutes{\i}\N{\i1}of Baghdad, Cairo,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.97,0:09:30.51,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and other Islamic capitols.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.54,0:09:34.08,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Instead of burning books,{\i}\N{\i1}the caliphs sent emissaries{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.11,0:09:37.05,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}around the world{\i}\N{\i1}in search of books.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.83,0:09:55.23,English1,,0,0,0,,The caliphs lavishly funded\Nprojects to translate, study,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.27,0:09:57.47,English1,,0,0,0,,and preserve them\Nfor future generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.50,0:10:00.44,English1,,0,0,0,,Much of the light of Ancient\NGreek science would have been
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.47,0:10:02.91,English1,,0,0,0,,permanently extinguished\Nwithout their efforts.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.94,0:10:05.74,English1,,0,0,0,,The reawakening to science\Nthat took place in Europe,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.78,0:10:08.81,English1,,0,0,0,,hundreds of years later,\Nwas kindled by a flame
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.85,0:10:10.08,English1,,0,0,0,,that had been long tended
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.12,0:10:12.98,English1,,0,0,0,,by Islamic scholars\Nand scientists.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.02,0:10:16.55,English1,,0,0,0,,The Arabs also imported ideas\Nfrom India to the West,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.59,0:10:19.16,English1,,0,0,0,,including the so-called\NArabic numerals
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.19,0:10:21.46,English1,,0,0,0,,that we all use today,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.49,0:10:24.29,English1,,0,0,0,,and the concept of zero...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.97,0:10:28.43,English1,,0,0,0,,which comes in handy
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.47,0:10:31.90,English1,,0,0,0,,when you want to write\N"billions and billions."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.94,0:10:34.91,English1,,0,0,0,,Arabic astronomy was\Nso influential,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.94,0:10:36.97,English1,,0,0,0,,that we still call most\Nof the bright stars
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.01,0:10:38.81,English1,,0,0,0,,by their Arabic names.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.84,0:10:43.91,English1,,0,0,0,,And the "al's" in algebra,\Nalgorithm, alchemy, and alcohol
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.95,0:10:45.65,English1,,0,0,0,,are just some\Nof the traces left
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.68,0:10:50.15,English1,,0,0,0,,from the time when Arabic\Nwas the language of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.06,0:10:54.79,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In the 11th century,{\i}\N{\i1}Ibn al-Hazen set about trying{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.83,0:10:58.86,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to test his ideas about light{\i}\N{\i1}and how we see.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.90,0:11:02.13,English1,,0,0,0,,So we devised an experiment\Nto determine how light moves.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.17,0:11:04.54,English1,,0,0,0,,We erected a tent\Nin full daylight
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.57,0:11:07.67,English1,,0,0,0,,and sealed it tightly so that\Nonly a single ray of light
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.71,0:11:10.44,English1,,0,0,0,,could pierce its inner darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.48,0:11:12.78,English1,,0,0,0,,With little more than his brains
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.81,0:11:15.05,English1,,0,0,0,,and a straight\Npiece of wood-- a ruler--
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.08,0:11:16.95,English1,,0,0,0,,al-Hazen had accomplished\Na great leap forward
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.98,0:11:18.52,English1,,0,0,0,,in the history of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.55,0:11:22.55,English1,,0,0,0,,He discovered that\Nlight moves in straight lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.73,0:11:29.69,English1,,0,0,0,,But he was just getting started.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.73,0:11:33.13,English1,,0,0,0,,Al-Hazen figured out that\Nthe key to forming any image--
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.16,0:11:36.20,English1,,0,0,0,,whether you're talking about\Nan eye or camera obscura--
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.23,0:11:38.90,English1,,0,0,0,,is a small opening to restrict\Nthe light that can enter
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.94,0:11:40.80,English1,,0,0,0,,an otherwise darkened chamber.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.84,0:11:43.71,English1,,0,0,0,,That aperture\Nexcludes the chaos
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.74,0:11:46.41,English1,,0,0,0,,of extraneous light rays\Nthat surround us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.44,0:11:48.08,English1,,0,0,0,,The smaller the aperture,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.11,0:11:50.65,English1,,0,0,0,,the fewer directions\Nthat light can come from.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.68,0:11:52.85,English1,,0,0,0,,And that makes\Nthe image sharper.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.88,0:11:55.65,English1,,0,0,0,,So instead of being blinded\Nby the light,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.69,0:11:58.86,English1,,0,0,0,,we can see everything\Nit has to show us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.89,0:12:02.19,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Al-Hazen made his own{\i}\N{\i1}camera obscura{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.23,0:12:04.26,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and dazzled the caliphs.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.30,0:12:07.36,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A camera obscura works best{\i}\N{\i1}in bright light.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.40,0:12:11.20,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The stars of the night sky{\i}\N{\i1}are way too dim for this.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.24,0:12:14.54,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We somehow need a bigger{\i}\N{\i1}opening to collect light,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.57,0:12:17.01,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but we also need{\i}\N{\i1}to maintain focus.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.04,0:12:19.68,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A telescope collects light{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.71,0:12:22.01,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}from any spot{\i}\N{\i1}in its field of view{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.05,0:12:25.02,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}across the entire lens{\i}\N{\i1}or mirror,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.05,0:12:28.75,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}an opening much larger{\i}\N{\i1}than the camera obscura hole.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.79,0:12:32.69,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This is one{\i}\N{\i1}of the first telescopes...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.72,0:12:36.79,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the one that Galileo looked{\i}\N{\i1}through in 1609.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.83,0:12:41.07,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}With it, he pulled aside{\i}\N{\i1}the heavy curtain of night{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.10,0:12:44.00,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and began to discover{\i}\N{\i1}the cosmos.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.61,0:12:58.62,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The lens made it possible{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.65,0:13:01.72,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}for a telescope to have a much{\i}\N{\i1}larger light-collecting area{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.75,0:13:04.05,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}than our eyes have.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.09,0:13:07.49,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Big buckets catch more rain{\i}\N{\i1}than small ones.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.53,0:13:10.43,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Modern telescopes have larger{\i}\N{\i1}collecting areas,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.46,0:13:12.13,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}highly sensitive detectors,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.16,0:13:15.07,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and they track the same object{\i}\N{\i1}for hours at a time{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.10,0:13:18.44,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to accumulate as much{\i}\N{\i1}of its light as possible.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.47,0:13:21.24,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Space-based telescopes{\i}\N{\i1}such as the Hubble,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.27,0:13:23.11,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}have captured light{\i}\N{\i1}from the most distant{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.14,0:13:24.78,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and ancient galaxies,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.81,0:13:27.98,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}giving us vastly clearer{\i}\N{\i1}pictures of the cosmos.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.61,0:13:33.32,English1,,0,0,0,,Al-Hazen discovered how images\Nare formed by light,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.35,0:13:35.69,English1,,0,0,0,,but that was far\Nfrom his greatest achievement.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.72,0:13:38.42,English1,,0,0,0,,Ibn al-Hazen was the first\Nperson ever
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.46,0:13:41.13,English1,,0,0,0,,to set down\Nthe rules of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.16,0:13:43.66,English1,,0,0,0,,He created\Nan error-correcting mechanism,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.70,0:13:46.16,English1,,0,0,0,,a systematic and relentless way
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.20,0:13:48.83,English1,,0,0,0,,to sift out misconceptions\Nin our thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.87,0:13:53.84,English1,,0,0,0,,Finding truth is difficult...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.87,0:13:56.84,English1,,0,0,0,,and the road to it is rough.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.88,0:13:59.14,English1,,0,0,0,,As seekers after truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.18,0:14:02.28,English1,,0,0,0,,you will be wise to withhold\Njudgment and not simply put
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.31,0:14:05.18,English1,,0,0,0,,your trust in the writings\Nof the ancients.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.22,0:14:09.02,English1,,0,0,0,,You must question and critically\Nexamine those writings
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.05,0:14:11.56,English1,,0,0,0,,from every side.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.59,0:14:14.83,English1,,0,0,0,,You must submit only\Nto argument and experiment
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.86,0:14:18.23,English1,,0,0,0,,and not to the sayings\Nof any person.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.26,0:14:20.80,English1,,0,0,0,,For every human being\Nis vulnerable
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.83,0:14:23.50,English1,,0,0,0,,to all kinds of imperfection.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.54,0:14:25.97,English1,,0,0,0,,As seekers after truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.00,0:14:28.34,English1,,0,0,0,,we must also suspect\Nand question
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.37,0:14:31.98,English1,,0,0,0,,our own ideas as we perform\Nour investigations,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.01,0:14:36.91,English1,,0,0,0,,to avoid falling into prejudice\Nor careless thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.95,0:14:42.19,English1,,0,0,0,,Take this course, and truth\Nwill be revealed to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.07,0:15:02.24,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This is the method of science.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.27,0:15:05.08,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So powerful that it's carried{\i}\N{\i1}our robotic emissaries{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.11,0:15:08.55,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to the edge of{\i}\N{\i1}the solar system and beyond.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.28,0:15:12.58,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It has doubled our lifespan,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.62,0:15:14.38,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}made the lost worlds{\i}\N{\i1}of the past{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.42,0:15:16.42,English1,,0,0,0,,come alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.82,0:15:20.06,English1,,0,0,0,,Science has enabled us\Nto predict events
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.09,0:15:22.56,English1,,0,0,0,,in the distant future...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.59,0:15:26.06,English1,,0,0,0,,and to communicate with each\Nother at the speed of light,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.10,0:15:28.70,English1,,0,0,0,,as I am with you,\Nright at this moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.73,0:15:30.77,English1,,0,0,0,,This way of thinking\Nhas given us powers
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.80,0:15:34.44,English1,,0,0,0,,that al-Hazen himself\Nwould have regarded as wizardry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.94,0:15:42.31,English1,,0,0,0,,But it was he who put us\Non this rough, endless road.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.18,0:15:47.05,English1,,0,0,0,,And now it has taken us\Nto a place
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.09,0:15:51.79,English1,,0,0,0,,where even light itself\Nis enshrouded in darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.09,0:16:02.22,English1,,0,0,0,,Light has properties unlike\Nanything else
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.26,0:16:04.13,English1,,0,0,0,,in the realm\Nof human existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.16,0:16:06.30,English1,,0,0,0,,Take the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.33,0:16:08.43,English1,,0,0,0,,The basic particle of light,\Nthe photon,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.46,0:16:11.13,English1,,0,0,0,,is born traveling\N{\i1}at{\i} the speed of light
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.17,0:16:13.94,English1,,0,0,0,,as it emerges from\Nan atom or a molecule.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.97,0:16:16.10,English1,,0,0,0,,A photon never knows\Nany other speed,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.14,0:16:18.94,English1,,0,0,0,,and we've not found another\Nphenomenon that accelerates
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.98,0:16:21.91,English1,,0,0,0,,from zero to top speed\Ninstantaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.95,0:16:24.15,English1,,0,0,0,,Nothing else\Ncould move as fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.18,0:16:26.82,English1,,0,0,0,,When we try to accelerate other\Nparticles closer and closer
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.85,0:16:29.55,English1,,0,0,0,,to the speed of light,\Nthey resist more and more,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.59,0:16:31.32,English1,,0,0,0,,as though they're getting\Nheavier and heavier.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.35,0:16:32.79,English1,,0,0,0,,No experiment yet devised
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.82,0:16:36.83,English1,,0,0,0,,has ever made a particle\Nmove as fast as light.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.50,0:16:46.13,English1,,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.17,0:16:48.34,English1,,0,0,0,,You hear something?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.37,0:16:50.51,English1,,0,0,0,,Where was I? Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.54,0:16:54.61,English1,,0,0,0,,I don't know anything else\Nin life that behaves like light.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.64,0:16:58.08,English1,,0,0,0,,I cannot reconcile\Nits strange properties
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.11,0:17:00.75,English1,,0,0,0,,with everything else\Nmy senses tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.78,0:17:03.75,English1,,0,0,0,,Our urge to trust\Nour senses overpowers
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.79,0:17:05.85,English1,,0,0,0,,what our measuring devices\Ntell us about
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.89,0:17:07.79,English1,,0,0,0,,the actual nature of reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.82,0:17:09.99,English1,,0,0,0,,Our senses work fine\Nfor life-size objects
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.03,0:17:11.83,English1,,0,0,0,,moving at mammal speeds,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.86,0:17:16.47,English1,,0,0,0,,but are ill-adapted for the\Nwonderland laws of lightspeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.64,0:17:24.01,English1,,0,0,0,,We don't even know why\Nthere's a cosmic speed limit.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.04,0:17:27.48,English1,,0,0,0,,Time stands still when you're\Ntraveling at the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.51,0:17:29.98,English1,,0,0,0,,What{\i1} is{\i} light, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.52,0:17:37.02,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Isaac Newton's enduring{\i}\N{\i1}fascination with light{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.05,0:17:39.22,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}began when he was a child...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.66,0:17:44.09,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}in this very house.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.17,0:17:53.34,English1,,0,0,0,,By the time he was in his 20s,\NNewton became the first person
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.37,0:17:56.54,English1,,0,0,0,,to decipher the mystery\Nof the rainbow.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.24,0:18:03.55,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Newton discovered that some{\i}\N{\i1}light, or white light,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.58,0:18:06.55,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}is a mixture of all the colors{\i}\N{\i1}of the rainbow.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.09,0:18:11.15,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Major discovery.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.19,0:18:13.72,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He named the displays of colors{\i}\N{\i1}a "spectrum"{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.76,0:18:18.03,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}from the Latin for "phantom"{\i}\N{\i1}or "apparition."{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.27,0:18:32.24,English1,,0,0,0,,Begging your pardon,\NMaster Newton,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.28,0:18:34.98,English1,,0,0,0,,the cook frets that your dinner\Nwill spoil, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.88,0:18:40.05,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}No, Isaac, don't{\i}\N{\i1}put the magnifying glass down!{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.08,0:18:43.85,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Something even more amazing{\i}\N{\i1}is hidden in the light--{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.89,0:18:46.39,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}a code, a key to the cosmos.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.16,0:18:57.07,English1,,0,0,0,,Isaac Newton didn't miss much,\Nbut that one was a beaut.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.10,0:19:00.20,English1,,0,0,0,,He just walked right past\Nthe door to a hidden universe;
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.24,0:19:04.27,English1,,0,0,0,,a door that would not swing open\Nagain for another 150 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.31,0:19:06.61,English1,,0,0,0,,It would fall\Non another scientist,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.64,0:19:08.31,English1,,0,0,0,,working in the year 1800,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.34,0:19:10.31,English1,,0,0,0,,to stumble\Non a piece of evidence
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.35,0:19:13.35,English1,,0,0,0,,for the unseen worlds\Nthat surround us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.92,0:19:19.35,English1,,0,0,0,,By night, William Herschel\Nscanned the heavens
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.39,0:19:21.86,English1,,0,0,0,,with the largest telescope\Nof his time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.89,0:19:24.83,English1,,0,0,0,,By day, Herschel performed\Nexperiments.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.86,0:19:27.50,English1,,0,0,0,,From Newton's earlier work,\Nit was known that sunlight
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.53,0:19:29.90,English1,,0,0,0,,is a blend of different colors.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.93,0:19:32.30,English1,,0,0,0,,And everyone knew,\Njust from being outside,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.33,0:19:34.53,English1,,0,0,0,,that sunlight carries heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.07,0:19:38.07,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}William Herschel asked{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.11,0:19:40.67,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}whether some colors of light{\i}\N{\i1}carry more heat than others.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.71,0:19:44.81,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The nature of scientific genius{\i}\N{\i1}is to question{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.85,0:19:47.65,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}what the rest of us{\i}\N{\i1}take for granted...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.68,0:19:50.25,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and then do the experiment.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.29,0:19:55.72,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The thermometer that Herschel{\i}\N{\i1}placed outside the spectrum{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.76,0:19:57.76,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}was his control.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.46,0:20:01.36,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The control in any experiment{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.39,0:20:04.03,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}always lacks{\i}\N{\i1}the factor being tested.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.06,0:20:06.16,English1,,0,0,0,,That way, you know\N{\i1}if what you're testing is{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.20,0:20:08.30,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}really the thing responsible{\i}\N{\i1}for the observation.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.43,0:20:10.74,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In Herschel's experiment,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.77,0:20:12.37,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the relationship between{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.40,0:20:13.77,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}color and temperature{\i}\N{\i1}was being tested,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.81,0:20:16.88,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and so his control was{\i}\N{\i1}a thermometer{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.91,0:20:18.58,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}over the part{\i}\N{\i1}of the white sheet{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.61,0:20:21.91,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}that was not illuminated{\i}\N{\i1}by sunlight at all.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.25,0:20:25.78,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There's that sound again.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.82,0:20:28.55,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What is that?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.29,0:20:36.79,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Okay, red light is warmer{\i}\N{\i1}than blue light.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.83,0:20:41.90,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Interesting discovery,{\i}\N{\i1}but not exactly revolutionary.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.42,0:21:07.12,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}No, there's nothing wrong{\i}\N{\i1}with your thermometer.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.16,0:21:10.52,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You've just discovered{\i}\N{\i1}a new kind of light.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.37,0:21:22.44,English1,,0,0,0,,Herschel was the first\Nto detect this unseen presence
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.47,0:21:25.67,English1,,0,0,0,,lurking just below\Nthe red end of the spectrum.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.71,0:21:28.61,English1,,0,0,0,,That's why it came\Nto be called "infrared."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.64,0:21:30.81,English1,,0,0,0,,"Infra" is Latin\Nfor the word "below."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.84,0:21:32.41,English1,,0,0,0,,It's invisible.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.45,0:21:34.81,English1,,0,0,0,,Our eyes are not sensitive\Nto this kind of light,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.85,0:21:37.72,English1,,0,0,0,,but our skin is--\Nwe feel it as heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.75,0:21:39.55,English1,,0,0,0,,Now, that's\Na really big discovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.59,0:21:41.99,English1,,0,0,0,,But far greater secrets\Nwere still hiding
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.02,0:21:44.49,English1,,0,0,0,,deep inside the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.38,0:21:52.41,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}At about the\Nsame time that William Herschel{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.45,0:21:55.35,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}was discovering infrared light{\i}\N{\i1}in his parlor in England,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.38,0:21:57.85,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}a young boy named{\i}\N{\i1}Joseph Fraunhofer{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.89,0:22:00.35,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}was trapped{\i}\N{\i1}in hopeless drudgery.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.39,0:22:03.32,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He stood over a cauldron{\i}\N{\i1}of toxic chemicals{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.36,0:22:05.73,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and endlessly stirred.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.63,0:22:10.43,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Joseph had been orphaned{\i}\N{\i1}at the age of 11{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.46,0:22:14.27,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and given to a harsh master{\i}\N{\i1}named Weichselberger,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.30,0:22:17.24,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the royal mirror-maker.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.27,0:22:19.54,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He prevented Joseph{\i}\N{\i1}from going to school.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.57,0:22:22.78,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Instead, Joseph labored in{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.81,0:22:24.74,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the glass-making{\i}\N{\i1}workshop by day,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.78,0:22:27.25,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and tended to the master's{\i}\N{\i1}household chores by night.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.75,0:22:34.25,English1,,0,0,0,,Hurry up, stupid!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.29,0:22:37.22,English1,,0,0,0,,And remember, no reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.59,0:22:44.43,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Until Joseph got his big break.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.46,0:22:48.56,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Weichselberger's{\i}\N{\i1}house collapsed.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.61,0:23:08.48,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Maximilian, the future{\i}\N{\i1}king of Bavaria,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.52,0:23:10.42,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}hurried to the scene{\i}\N{\i1}of the calamity{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.45,0:23:11.99,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to see if he could help.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.02,0:23:14.45,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Maximilian was known for{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.49,0:23:16.09,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}taking an interest{\i}\N{\i1}in his subjects,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.12,0:23:18.33,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}which was highly unusual{\i}\N{\i1}for its time.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.21,0:23:35.34,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In attracting the concern{\i}\N{\i1}of the future king of Bavaria,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.38,0:23:36.98,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}young Joseph Fraunhofer{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.01,0:23:39.81,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}found an aperture into{\i}\N{\i1}a different universe.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.85,0:23:42.28,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And not just for himself.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.09,0:23:46.85,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Prince Maximilian{\i}\N{\i1}gave Joseph money{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.89,0:23:48.69,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and asked his privy councilor{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.72,0:23:50.16,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to provide further{\i}\N{\i1}help to the boy,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.19,0:23:52.56,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}should it be needed.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.43,0:24:00.13,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Weichselberger continued{\i}\N{\i1}to exploit him{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.17,0:24:02.47,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and prevent him{\i}\N{\i1}from attending school.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.50,0:24:04.54,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But the prince's councilor{\i}\N{\i1}intervened,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.57,0:24:08.08,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}offering Joseph a position{\i}\N{\i1}at the Optical Institute.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.11,0:24:13.25,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This small gesture of kindness{\i}\N{\i1}really paid off.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.59,0:24:28.43,English1,,0,0,0,,By the time he was 27,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.46,0:24:30.70,English1,,0,0,0,,Joseph Fraunhofer was\Nthe world's leading designer
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.73,0:24:32.73,English1,,0,0,0,,of high-quality lenses,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.77,0:24:35.44,English1,,0,0,0,,telescopes and other\Noptical instruments.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.47,0:24:39.34,English1,,0,0,0,,His firm was housed here,\Nin the old Benediktbeuren Abbey.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.37,0:24:41.54,English1,,0,0,0,,In the early 19th century,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.58,0:24:44.88,English1,,0,0,0,,this was top-secret,\Nultra-high technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.92,0:24:50.12,English1,,0,0,0,,The Benedictine monks\Nof earlier times
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.15,0:24:52.12,English1,,0,0,0,,had taken a vow of secrecy.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.15,0:24:54.12,English1,,0,0,0,,This local tradition,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.16,0:24:55.62,English1,,0,0,0,,and the ability\Nto restrict access
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.66,0:24:57.19,English1,,0,0,0,,to Fraunhofer's laboratory,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.23,0:24:59.19,English1,,0,0,0,,allowed him to maintain control
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.23,0:25:02.30,English1,,0,0,0,,of trade and state secrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.40,0:25:09.70,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Fraunhofer was experimenting{\i}\N{\i1}with prisms{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.74,0:25:13.14,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to find the best types of glass{\i}\N{\i1}for precision lenses.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.17,0:25:15.88,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}How, he wondered,{\i}\N{\i1}could he get a better look{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.91,0:25:17.91,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}at the spectrum that{\i}\N{\i1}a prism produced?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.08,0:25:24.89,English1,,0,0,0,,Friedrich, bring me\Nthe theodolite, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.92,0:25:27.82,English1,,0,0,0,,Okay, while Fraunhofer\Nsets up his theodolite--
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.86,0:25:29.66,English1,,0,0,0,,it's a kind of telescope--
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.69,0:25:32.99,English1,,0,0,0,,I want to show you something\Nin another part of the abbey.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.63,0:25:41.37,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Sound waves are{\i}\N{\i1}so beautiful to hear.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.20,0:25:47.91,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Imagine how beautiful{\i}\N{\i1}they'd be to see.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.94,0:25:51.15,English1,,0,0,0,,You ever wondered why organ\Npipes have different lengths?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.38,0:25:54.62,English1,,0,0,0,,I press a key...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.12,0:25:58.52,English1,,0,0,0,,it sends compressed air
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.55,0:25:59.79,English1,,0,0,0,,into a particular pipe,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.82,0:26:01.62,English1,,0,0,0,,producing sound waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.66,0:26:04.36,English1,,0,0,0,,If we could slow the sound waves\Ndown a few hundred times,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.39,0:26:06.53,English1,,0,0,0,,they would look like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.23,0:26:11.87,English1,,0,0,0,,The length of the pipe
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.90,0:26:13.33,English1,,0,0,0,,determines the length\Nof the sound wave
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.37,0:26:14.84,English1,,0,0,0,,that can fit inside it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.87,0:26:16.94,English1,,0,0,0,,A short pipe gives you\Na short sound wave.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.97,0:26:21.71,English1,,0,0,0,,Short sounds waves have\Nhigh pitch, or frequency.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.22,0:26:29.88,English1,,0,0,0,,Let's stop the waves\Nfor a better look.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.26,0:26:36.19,English1,,0,0,0,,The distance between\Nadjacent waves
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.22,0:26:37.99,English1,,0,0,0,,is called the wavelength.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.03,0:26:40.53,English1,,0,0,0,,A long pipe gives you\Na long sound wave
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.56,0:26:42.93,English1,,0,0,0,,with a low pitch,\Nor low frequency.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.48,0:27:37.38,English1,,0,0,0,,The medieval manuscript of\Nthis music, "Carmina Burana,"
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.42,0:27:40.59,English1,,0,0,0,,was discovered\Nin this very abbey.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.79,0:27:46.23,English1,,0,0,0,,Sound waves can't travel\Nthrough a vacuum.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.26,0:27:48.13,English1,,0,0,0,,They need matter to ride on,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.16,0:27:51.63,English1,,0,0,0,,like molecules of air,\Nor water, or rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.67,0:27:53.77,English1,,0,0,0,,But light waves fly solo.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.80,0:27:55.97,English1,,0,0,0,,They can move\Nthrough empty space.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.00,0:27:57.60,English1,,0,0,0,,And fast--
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.64,0:28:00.74,English1,,0,0,0,,a million times faster\Nthan sound waves in air.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.78,0:28:02.74,English1,,0,0,0,,And the wavelengths\Nof the light we see
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.78,0:28:05.28,English1,,0,0,0,,are so much shorter\Nthan sound waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.31,0:28:08.15,English1,,0,0,0,,About 50,000 light waves
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.18,0:28:10.62,English1,,0,0,0,,would fit right in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.79,0:28:13.32,English1,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.36,0:28:14.79,English1,,0,0,0,,Fraunhofer.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.43,0:28:22.76,English1,,0,0,0,,Just in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.80,0:28:24.43,English1,,0,0,0,,We didn't miss it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.47,0:28:26.63,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Just as the wavelength of sound{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.67,0:28:28.64,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}determines the pitch{\i}\N{\i1}that we hear,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.67,0:28:30.14,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the wavelength of light{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.17,0:28:32.61,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}determines the color{\i}\N{\i1}that we see.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.64,0:28:35.08,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But how does a prism{\i}\N{\i1}spread out the colors{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.11,0:28:37.61,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}concealed in{\i}\N{\i1}a beam of sunlight?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.65,0:28:41.58,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}When light travels{\i}\N{\i1}through air or space,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.62,0:28:43.98,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}all its colors move{\i}\N{\i1}at the same speed.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.02,0:28:48.79,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But when it hits glass{\i}\N{\i1}at an angle,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.82,0:28:51.23,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the light slows down{\i}\N{\i1}and changes direction.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.79,0:28:54.76,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Inside the prism,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.80,0:28:56.80,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}each color moves{\i}\N{\i1}at a different speed.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.14,0:29:02.94,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In glass, violet light,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.97,0:29:05.14,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}which is carried by{\i}\N{\i1}the shortest waves we see,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.17,0:29:07.17,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}slows down more than red light,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.21,0:29:09.64,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}which has the longest waves.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.48,0:29:13.88,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}These changes in speed{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.92,0:29:16.45,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}pry the colors apart,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.48,0:29:18.29,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}sending their waves off{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.32,0:29:20.72,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}in slightly different{\i}\N{\i1}directions.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.92,0:29:23.92,English1,,0,0,0,,That's how a prism works.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.06,0:29:28.33,English1,,0,0,0,,If I seem unduly\Nemotional about this,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.36,0:29:31.17,English1,,0,0,0,,it's because Joseph Fraunhofer\Nis about to do
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.20,0:29:34.70,English1,,0,0,0,,what Isaac Newton\Ncould've done, but didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.74,0:29:36.80,English1,,0,0,0,,And it'll have a powerful effect
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.84,0:29:38.67,English1,,0,0,0,,on the course of my own life.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.70,0:30:03.73,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You are witnessing the marriage{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.77,0:30:05.37,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}of physics and astronomy,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.40,0:30:09.27,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the birth of my own{\i}\N{\i1}field of science,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.30,0:30:11.74,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}astrophysics.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.74,0:30:15.51,English1,,0,0,0,,Written in the light,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.54,0:30:18.95,English1,,0,0,0,,in those vertical black lines...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.38,0:30:23.35,English1,,0,0,0,,is secret code.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.39,0:30:26.19,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Fraunhofer looked at them,{\i}\N{\i1}and wondered...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.22,0:30:28.22,English1,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.13,0:30:33.46,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A code that comes to us{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.50,0:30:35.93,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}from an alien universe.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.29,0:30:47.54,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What is the message{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.63,0:30:51.23,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}written in these dark,{\i}\N{\i1}vertical lines?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.30,0:30:58.37,English1,,0,0,0,,It took a hundred years\Nof thinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.41,0:31:01.71,English1,,0,0,0,,questioning, searching\Nto decipher it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.26,0:31:23.40,English1,,0,0,0,,Lovely, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.43,0:31:24.97,English1,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.00,0:31:28.47,English1,,0,0,0,,There are many layers to\Nthe fine structure of beauty...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.50,0:31:31.64,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the chemistry of the Earth{\i}\N{\i1}and its atmosphere...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.67,0:31:34.61,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the evolution of life...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.64,0:31:38.21,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Many distinct threads.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.25,0:31:41.31,English1,,0,0,0,,Let's just examine one,\Nat the surface...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.35,0:31:43.75,English1,,0,0,0,,the colors of nature\Nthat dazzle us.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.78,0:31:46.89,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What's really happening?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.92,0:31:48.79,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}How does the red, the blue...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.82,0:31:51.79,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the astonishing palette{\i}\N{\i1}of nature's colors...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.80,0:31:58.43,English1,,0,0,0,,how do they happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.10,0:32:03.27,English1,,0,0,0,,Light waves of different lengths\Nfrom the Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.30,0:32:04.70,English1,,0,0,0,,strike the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.11,0:32:08.14,English1,,0,0,0,,The petals of these\Nparticular flowers
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.18,0:32:09.74,English1,,0,0,0,,absorb all the low-energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.78,0:32:12.01,English1,,0,0,0,,long red wavelengths of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.05,0:32:13.75,English1,,0,0,0,,But the petals reflect
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.78,0:32:17.08,English1,,0,0,0,,the shorter, high-energy\Nblue wavelengths.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.12,0:32:19.85,English1,,0,0,0,,That interaction\Nbetween starlight and petal--
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.89,0:32:21.86,English1,,0,0,0,,or water, or Van Gogh--
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.89,0:32:23.46,English1,,0,0,0,,is what makes blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.49,0:32:25.63,English1,,0,0,0,,The longest waves,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.66,0:32:27.46,English1,,0,0,0,,the ones we see as red,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.50,0:32:30.06,English1,,0,0,0,,have the lowest energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.00,0:32:35.34,English1,,0,0,0,,Color is the way\Nour eyes perceive
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.37,0:32:37.24,English1,,0,0,0,,how energetic light waves are.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.07,0:32:40.77,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A sunset...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.81,0:32:42.94,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}a flag...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.98,0:32:45.38,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the eyes of your beloved...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.41,0:32:47.15,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}that shiny new car.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.18,0:32:49.15,English1,,0,0,0,,The feelings they inspire
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.18,0:32:50.98,English1,,0,0,0,,happen when something inside you
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.02,0:32:53.49,English1,,0,0,0,,is triggered by\Na particular variation
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.52,0:32:56.99,English1,,0,0,0,,in the frequency and\Nenergy of light waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.76,0:32:59.89,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And the secret message?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.93,0:33:01.63,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Those black vertical lines{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.66,0:33:03.66,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}in Fraunhofer's spectrum?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.70,0:33:05.80,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What makes them?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.83,0:33:08.00,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They occur when the light waves{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.04,0:33:10.80,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}of those particular colors{\i}\N{\i1}are being absorbed.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.84,0:33:13.37,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It happens on another level{\i}\N{\i1}of reality,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.41,0:33:16.41,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}far smaller than the world{\i}\N{\i1}we're used to operating in.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.44,0:33:19.01,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}To get there,{\i}\N{\i1}we'll need to become{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.05,0:33:21.78,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}ten billion times smaller{\i}\N{\i1}than we are.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.55,0:33:26.92,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We could pick{\i}\N{\i1}any one of these atoms.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.95,0:33:30.02,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But let's go{\i}\N{\i1}for the hydrogen atom.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.06,0:33:32.53,English1,,0,0,0,,The hydrogen atom is\Nthe most plentiful kind
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.56,0:33:34.93,English1,,0,0,0,,of atom in the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.96,0:33:37.36,English1,,0,0,0,,And the simplest.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.87,0:33:48.04,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It has only one electron.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.08,0:33:50.58,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And only one proton.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.61,0:33:52.68,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We've entered{\i}\N{\i1}the quantum realm.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.71,0:33:54.51,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It doesn't correspond{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.55,0:33:57.28,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to ordinary human experience.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.32,0:34:00.52,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Common sense is{\i}\N{\i1}no help here at all.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.56,0:34:03.56,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Take the hydrogen atom's{\i}\N{\i1}electron, for example.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.49,0:34:07.73,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In an atom, an electron{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.76,0:34:09.46,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}doesn't exist between orbitals.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.50,0:34:11.26,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It disappears from one orbital{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.30,0:34:13.93,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and reappears in another.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.97,0:34:15.77,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's as if you took an elevator{\i}\N{\i1}from the second floor{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.80,0:34:19.07,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to the fourth floor,{\i}\N{\i1}but ceased to exist in between.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.11,0:34:20.81,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And another thing.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.84,0:34:23.78,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Quantum elevators only stop{\i}\N{\i1}at certain floors.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.81,0:34:27.21,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The sizes of the electron{\i}\N{\i1}orbits are strictly limited,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.25,0:34:30.08,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and different{\i}\N{\i1}for the atoms of every element.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.62,0:34:33.95,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's why the elements{\i}\N{\i1}are different.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.99,0:34:35.32,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The chemistry{\i}\N{\i1}of anything is determined{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.36,0:34:36.92,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}by its electron orbits.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.96,0:34:39.83,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The force that holds{\i}\N{\i1}an electron in orbit{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.86,0:34:41.66,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}has nothing to do with gravity.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.70,0:34:45.23,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's a force{\i}\N{\i1}of electrical attraction.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.27,0:34:47.57,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The electron dances a wavy ring{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.60,0:34:49.84,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}around the central nucleus{\i}\N{\i1}of a hydrogen atom.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.87,0:34:52.64,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And makes quantum leaps{\i}\N{\i1}from orbit to orbit.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.67,0:34:53.94,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Up or down.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.98,0:34:55.34,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The larger the orbit,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.38,0:34:57.41,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the greater the energy{\i}\N{\i1}of an electron.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.45,0:34:59.81,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}An electron has{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.85,0:35:01.98,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to get energy to leap{\i}\N{\i1}to a larger orbit.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.02,0:35:04.82,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And it has to lose energy{\i}\N{\i1}to jump back down.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.85,0:35:08.15,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Every upward leap{\i}\N{\i1}is caused by...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.19,0:35:11.59,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}an atom absorbing a light wave.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.63,0:35:15.43,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But we have no idea what causes{\i}\N{\i1}the downward leaps.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.46,0:35:19.03,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What we do know that such leaps{\i}\N{\i1}always produce a light wave{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.07,0:35:21.70,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}whose color matches{\i}\N{\i1}the energy difference{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.74,0:35:23.50,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}between the orbitals.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.41,0:35:32.81,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The Sun's surface radiates{\i}\N{\i1}light waves of all colors.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.85,0:35:34.65,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If you look at sunlight{\i}\N{\i1}through a prism,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.68,0:35:36.68,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}you'll see its spectrum.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.32,0:35:42.16,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}When you magnify the spectrum{\i}\N{\i1}with a telescope,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.19,0:35:44.06,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}as Joseph Fraunhofer did,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.09,0:35:45.66,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}you raise the curtain{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.69,0:35:48.90,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}on the electron dance{\i}\N{\i1}within the atom.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.93,0:35:51.13,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}When the energy{\i}\N{\i1}of the electron flags,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.17,0:35:52.83,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and it drops{\i}\N{\i1}to a lower orbital,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.87,0:35:55.24,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the light wave{\i}\N{\i1}it emits scatters.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.27,0:35:57.67,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Most of it doesn't reach us.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.71,0:35:59.24,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That leaves a dark gap{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.27,0:36:02.18,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}or black vertical line{\i}\N{\i1}in the spectrum.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.21,0:36:04.74,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}These dark lines{\i}\N{\i1}are the shadows{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.78,0:36:06.38,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}cast by hydrogen atoms{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.41,0:36:08.35,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}in the atmosphere of the Sun.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.38,0:36:11.08,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Sodium atoms cast{\i}\N{\i1}different shadows.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.12,0:36:14.19,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Their electrons dance{\i}\N{\i1}to a different tune.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.22,0:36:16.09,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A grain of table salt{\i}\N{\i1}is composed{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.12,0:36:17.92,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}of sodium and chlorine atoms.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.96,0:36:20.39,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Ten million billion of them{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.43,0:36:22.40,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}doing their crazy dances{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.43,0:36:25.27,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}in a single grain of salt.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.30,0:36:28.20,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And a single iron atom{\i}\N{\i1}with 26 electrons{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.24,0:36:30.57,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}is like a great{\i}\N{\i1}big production number{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.61,0:36:33.91,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}in a Broadway musical.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.31,0:36:40.21,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}When you look at a star{\i}\N{\i1}with a spectroscope,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.25,0:36:42.68,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}you see the dark lines{\i}\N{\i1}from all the elements{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.72,0:36:44.35,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}in its atmosphere.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.39,0:36:46.25,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Show me the spectrum{\i}\N{\i1}of anything,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.29,0:36:49.06,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}whether here on Earth{\i}\N{\i1}or from a distant star,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.09,0:36:52.13,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and I'll tell you{\i}\N{\i1}what it's made of.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.16,0:36:55.76,English1,,0,0,0,,Fraunhofer's lines are\Nthe atomic signatures
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.80,0:36:59.77,English1,,0,0,0,,of the elements writ large\Nacross the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.80,0:37:01.87,English1,,0,0,0,,As with every\Nother major revelation
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.90,0:37:04.40,English1,,0,0,0,,in the history of science,\Nit opened the way
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.44,0:37:07.41,English1,,0,0,0,,to newer and deeper mysteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.44,0:37:10.41,English1,,0,0,0,,And to the revelation\Nthat there were
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.44,0:37:13.48,English1,,0,0,0,,many more secrets\Nhiding in the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.43,0:37:24.36,English1,,0,0,0,,When Joseph Fraunhofer combined\Na prism with a telescope
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.37,0:37:26.63,English1,,0,0,0,,and turned it toward the skies,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.64,0:37:30.14,English1,,0,0,0,,he brought the stars\Nmuch closer to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.12,0:37:43.85,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}When he was only 39,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.85,0:37:46.02,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}he contracted a fatal illness.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.02,0:37:48.69,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Perhaps as a result of his{\i}\N{\i1}early and long-term exposure{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.69,0:37:51.62,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to the toxic chemicals{\i}\N{\i1}of glassmaking.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.63,0:37:55.63,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You never know where{\i}\N{\i1}the next genius will come from.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.57,0:38:04.07,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}How many of them do we leave{\i}\N{\i1}in the rubble?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.07,0:38:07.34,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The prince and his kingdom{\i}\N{\i1}were immeasurably enriched{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.34,0:38:10.71,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}by that act of kindness{\i}\N{\i1}to a poor orphan.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.71,0:38:13.15,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Fraunhofer's discoveries{\i}\N{\i1}transformed Bavaria{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.15,0:38:17.42,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}from a rural backwater{\i}\N{\i1}to a technological powerhouse.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.25,0:38:21.69,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}As he lay dying,{\i}\N{\i1}the government was desperate{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.69,0:38:24.59,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to preserve every shred{\i}\N{\i1}of his precious knowledge{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.59,0:38:26.89,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}about the high technology{\i}\N{\i1}of optical glass.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.93,0:38:31.87,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But it could only be divulged{\i}\N{\i1}to a person{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.87,0:38:34.07,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}with top security clearance--{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.07,0:38:35.84,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the director of the mint.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.92,0:38:55.52,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The government kept{\i}\N{\i1}Fraunhofer's technology{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.52,0:38:57.42,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}for making perfect{\i}\N{\i1}optical glass{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.43,0:39:00.69,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}a State secret{\i}\N{\i1}for another hundred years.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.70,0:39:02.70,English1,,0,0,0,,This would prove\Nto be a major obstacle
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.73,0:39:05.20,English1,,0,0,0,,for someone we'll meet later\Nin our journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.23,0:39:07.77,English1,,0,0,0,,But Fraunhofer would allow\Nno such secrecy
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.80,0:39:10.37,English1,,0,0,0,,where his pure scientific\Nresearch was concerned.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.40,0:39:14.01,English1,,0,0,0,,He knew that science requires\Nopenness to flourish;
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.04,0:39:18.08,English1,,0,0,0,,that our understanding of nature\Nbelongs to the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.11,0:39:21.01,English1,,0,0,0,,As soon as Fraunhofer discovered\Nthe spectral lines,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.05,0:39:23.58,English1,,0,0,0,,he published everything\Nhe knew about them.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.62,0:39:26.42,English1,,0,0,0,,And the reverberations\Nof his momentous discovery
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.45,0:39:29.22,English1,,0,0,0,,echo still.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.39,0:39:36.36,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}His spectral lines revealed{\i}\N{\i1}that the visible cosmos{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.40,0:39:39.67,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}is all made{\i}\N{\i1}of the same elements.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.70,0:39:45.17,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The planets...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.31,0:39:55.78,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The stars...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.15,0:40:02.29,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The galaxies...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.53,0:40:09.53,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We, ourselves,{\i}\N{\i1}and all of life...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.20,0:40:19.74,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The same star stuff.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.18,0:40:26.85,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He made it possible{\i}\N{\i1}for us to know{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.88,0:40:29.35,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}what's in the atmosphere{\i}\N{\i1}of other worlds.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.82,0:40:35.46,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And in galaxies millions{\i}\N{\i1}of light-years away.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.49,0:40:37.49,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Spectral lines revealed{\i}\N{\i1}not only the composition{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.52,0:40:39.99,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}of far-off objects,{\i}\N{\i1}but also their motion{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.03,0:40:42.20,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}towards or away from us.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.23,0:40:45.30,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Using them, we discovered{\i}\N{\i1}that our universe is expanding.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.33,0:40:48.90,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But perhaps the greatest{\i}\N{\i1}revelation of spectroscopy{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.94,0:40:51.74,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}is the discovery{\i}\N{\i1}of the thing it cannot see.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.75,0:40:59.91,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A hidden universe{\i}\N{\i1}of dark matter{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.95,0:41:03.18,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}six times more massive{\i}\N{\i1}than the familiar cosmos.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.22,0:41:05.38,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's made{\i}\N{\i1}of some mysterious substance{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.42,0:41:09.99,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}that does not emit, reflect{\i}\N{\i1}or absorb any kind of light.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.02,0:41:12.49,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We only know it's there{\i}\N{\i1}because of its gravity,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.53,0:41:14.59,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}which pulls on all the galaxies{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.63,0:41:17.36,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and speeds up the visible stars within them.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.37,0:41:24.84,English1,,0,0,0,,There are many more kinds of\Nlight than our eyes can see.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.87,0:41:28.27,English1,,0,0,0,,Confining our perception\Nof nature to visible light
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.31,0:41:30.61,English1,,0,0,0,,is like listening to music
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.64,0:41:32.21,English1,,0,0,0,,in only one octave.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.78,0:41:36.78,English1,,0,0,0,,There are so many more.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.82,0:41:38.75,English1,,0,0,0,,They differ only in wavelength,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.79,0:41:40.89,English1,,0,0,0,,but over a huge range.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.92,0:41:43.49,English1,,0,0,0,,For instance, infrared light...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.83,0:41:51.96,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the kind that William Herschel discovered{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.00,0:41:53.77,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Or X-ray light.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.84,0:42:00.91,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Or radio light.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.65,0:42:07.48,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Or in gamma-ray light.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.29,0:42:16.56,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}These are not just different{\i}\N{\i1}ways of seeing the same thing.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.59,0:42:18.16,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}These other kinds of light{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.19,0:42:21.79,English1,,0,0,0,,reveal different objects\Nand phenomena in the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.83,0:42:25.00,English1,,0,0,0,,In gamma-ray light, for example,\Nwe can see mysterious explosions
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.03,0:42:26.77,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}in distant galaxies{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.80,0:42:29.10,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}that we would otherwise miss.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.04,0:42:34.91,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And in microwave light,{\i}\N{\i1}we can see all the way back{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.94,0:42:37.34,English1,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to the birth of the universe.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.88,0:42:43.18,English1,,0,0,0,,We have only just opened our eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.87,0:43:08.48,English1,,0,0,0,,Sync and corrections by n17t01\Nwww.addic7ed.com
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.71,0:01:37.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}宇宙的年龄和大小
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.04,0:01:40.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}都被记录在光中
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.18,0:01:45.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}美丽的大自然和恒星的物质
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.05,0:01:48.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}时空的定律
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.46,0:01:51.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}原本就存在
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.46,0:01:53.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}但我们过去未能发现
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.49,0:01:57.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}直到我们拥有了更为强大的观察方式
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.36,0:02:01.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这种觉醒的故事有很多的开始
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.07,0:02:03.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}却不会结束
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.24,0:02:06.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}从不同时间和地方涌现出许多的英雄
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.47,0:02:09.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}中国古代的哲人
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.31,0:02:12.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}令11世纪伊拉克穆斯林统治者叹服的奇才
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.01,0:02:17.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}被苛刻奴役的德国可怜孤儿
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.92,0:02:20.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}每一位都带领我们前进一小步
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.39,0:02:24.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}去解开藏在光中的秘密
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.23,0:02:30.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}大多数的名字都已经被遗忘了
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.70,0:02:35.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}但在某处  很久前  某人的匆匆一瞥
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.24,0:02:39.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}注意到了光线展示出的神奇
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.93,0:03:01.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}谁知道呢
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.96,0:03:03.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}或许光线的偶然作为
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.76,0:03:05.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}为第一位艺术家带来了灵感
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.14,0:03:21.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这些都是怎么来的
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.21,0:03:24.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们是如何从小量聚居的
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.82,0:03:26.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,,采集者和猎人 进化而来的
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.99,0:03:30.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,成为世界文明的缔造者
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.79,0:03:34.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,中间的过程是怎样的
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.26,0:03:36.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,没有统一的答案
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.10,0:03:38.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,气候的变化  学会控制火
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.80,0:03:43.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}工具的发明  语言  耕种
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.34,0:03:46.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}都有各自的功劳
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.64,0:03:49.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}或许还有其他的
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.31,0:03:52.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}中国  2000多年前
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.48,0:03:55.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}一位名叫 墨子 的哲人 据说发现了
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.68,0:03:58.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}光线可以在密闭的宝库中
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.08,0:04:00.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}产生图像 （小孔成像）
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.35,0:04:05.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这描述的就是第一台照相机
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.83,0:04:07.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}暗箱
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.96,0:04:10.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}所有成像照相机的原型
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.36,0:04:13.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}包括给你带来图像的这台摄像机
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.67,0:04:16.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}利用光线这种有趣的现象
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.30,0:04:21.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}催生了首部的电影
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.31,0:04:27.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}墨子 光线大师  专治各种黑暗
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.11,0:04:28.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}军事天才
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.88,0:04:32.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}以智抑暴
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.05,0:04:34.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他最著名的成就是
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.05,0:04:36.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}穿行于战乱的国家间
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.19,0:04:37.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}运用巧妙的策略
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.96,0:04:39.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}劝导各方休战
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.03,0:04:43.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他是兼爱的倡导者
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.63,0:04:46.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}提倡消灭统治者带给人们的
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.73,0:04:50.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}贫困与不公
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.70,0:04:54.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}批判对于宗教和权威的盲从
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.57,0:04:56.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在他的著作中  你能发现
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.18,0:04:59.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}科学探索的早期萌芽
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.91,0:05:02.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}到墨子那个年代  中国人已经开始
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.88,0:05:06.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}用书籍记录他们的思想 至少上千年了
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.25,0:05:09.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}但我们对他的了解 依然仅是只字片语
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.22,0:05:11.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}通过许多由他和他的追随者
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.69,0:05:13.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}所著的文集而来
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.39,0:05:16.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}其中一篇 题为《非命》
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.56,0:05:19.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}立论一定要有三项标准 （故言必有三表）
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.70,0:05:22.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}推究来历 （有本之者）
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.24,0:05:23.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}是否可以由
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.94,0:05:26.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}普通人的观感再次验证的 （有原之者）
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.51,0:05:28.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}是否可以推广
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.27,0:05:30.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}并使大多数人受益 （有用之者）
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.05,0:05:37.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}墨子的思想流传很广
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.55,0:05:39.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}但他身后的数百年
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.89,0:05:42.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}秦始皇  第一位皇帝
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.86,0:05:45.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}统一了中国  独揽大权
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.93,0:05:48.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他将一片大陆变成了一个国家
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.53,0:05:51.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这个现在依然受他影响的国度  中国
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.97,0:05:59.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们大多数人对他的了解
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.47,0:06:02.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}来自守卫陵墓的7000件兵马俑
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.64,0:06:07.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在秦始皇的领导下
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.61,0:06:10.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为了巩固辽阔的帝国
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.25,0:06:11.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他采取极端的手段
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.95,0:06:14.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为所有事物都建立了标准
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.45,0:06:17.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,包括 铸造单一货币
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.42,0:06:19.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,统一度量衡
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.99,0:06:23.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,车辆与道路的宽度 （车同轨） 还有
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.83,0:06:26.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,中文书写形式的规范 （书同文）
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.07,0:06:31.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也包括了什么是可以写 什么是可以想的
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.14,0:06:33.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,秦始皇的哲学 唯一他认可的
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.94,0:06:35.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,称之 法家学说
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.58,0:06:38.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就如同它的字面意思
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.18,0:06:41.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,遵纪守法 否则呵呵
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.02,0:06:44.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这种哲学理论对于质疑权威
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.68,0:06:47.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}不是十分有利
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.76,0:06:54.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,百家思想的书籍
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.59,0:06:56.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,统统烧掉
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.26,0:06:59.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,以古讽今者
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.70,0:07:01.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,全家处斩
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.00,0:07:06.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}墨子和孔子的著作
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.14,0:07:08.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}还有其他哲人的作品
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.38,0:07:10.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}尽毁于世界历史上首次的焚书
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.38,0:07:12.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}数百名书生英勇抵抗
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.98,0:07:15.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}试图保护这些禁书
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.72,0:07:18.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在首都（咸阳）将他们活埋 （坑儒）
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.05,0:07:23.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,科学需要有自由的表达才能繁荣发展
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.89,0:07:27.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,需要无畏的质疑权威
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.29,0:07:29.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,开放的交流思想
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.90,0:07:33.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,墨子和他的追随者们所记载的
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.63,0:07:37.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,突发奇想都被抹杀了
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.40,0:07:42.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,影片的再次出现 已是另一个千年之后
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.91,0:07:46.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}幸运的是 我们的想象之舟
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.18,0:07:50.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}可以带我们去任何的空间和时间
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.85,0:08:00.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}中国和希腊的古人发现
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.55,0:08:02.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,光线可以展现出各种神奇
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.22,0:08:05.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是却没人去问
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.06,0:08:10.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,小孩子和天才们喜欢问的问题  为什么
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.36,0:08:13.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,直到一千年前
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.50,0:08:20.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}伊拉克的巴斯拉城
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.87,0:08:22.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}生活着另一位光线大师
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.87,0:08:28.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}海桑极度渴望了解自然
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.25,0:08:30.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他对一切都有疑问
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.38,0:08:34.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}特别是那些别人认为理所应当的事情
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.25,0:08:39.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们怎么能看到  他问
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.49,0:08:41.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}有些在他之前的伟大权威
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.89,0:08:45.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}认为光线从我们的眼中出发
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.50,0:08:49.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在物体上反射 然后返回我们的眼中
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.87,0:08:53.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}但海桑不认同 理由是恒星离我们那么远
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.77,0:08:56.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}什么东西可以从我们眼中射向星星
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.37,0:08:59.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}并在一眨眼的时间内返回
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.04,0:09:02.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}很有道理  但海桑并未止步
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.71,0:09:06.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他绞尽脑汁探索大自然的奥秘
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.02,0:09:10.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}当时他的文化对于新的见解与质疑是开放的态度
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.36,0:09:12.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}那是科学发展的黄金时代
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.86,0:09:15.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在伊斯兰世界
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.09,0:09:18.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}伊斯兰世界从西班牙的科索瓦
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.56,0:09:22.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}一直延伸到中亚的撒马尔罕
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.20,0:09:25.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}基督教和犹太教的学者被敬为上宾
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.24,0:09:27.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在开罗  巴格达的研究机构
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.97,0:09:30.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}和其他伊斯兰世界的中心
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.54,0:09:34.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}不同于秦始皇  哈里发们派遣使者\N（哈里发是穆斯林统治者的称号）
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.11,0:09:37.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在世界各地搜集书籍
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.83,0:09:55.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,哈里发们大量的资助将这些书籍
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.27,0:09:57.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,翻译 研究  并保存  流传后世
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.50,0:10:00.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,多亏了他们的努力  许多古希腊科学家的
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.47,0:10:02.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,成果才得以保存
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.94,0:10:05.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,对科学的狂热在欧洲再次兴起
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.78,0:10:08.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,发生在几百年后 多亏了伊斯兰学者和
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.85,0:10:10.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,科学家对这些文献的
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.12,0:10:12.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,精心呵护
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.02,0:10:16.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,阿拉伯人将新思想由印度传入西方
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.59,0:10:19.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,包括所谓的  阿拉伯数字
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.19,0:10:21.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们至今都在使用
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.49,0:10:24.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还有数字0
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.97,0:10:28.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,确实很方便
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.47,0:10:31.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,特别是当你书写 几十亿又几十亿时
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.94,0:10:34.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,阿拉伯天文学十分具有影响力
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.94,0:10:36.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们至今依然用阿拉伯语名字来称呼
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.01,0:10:38.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那些明亮的恒星
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.84,0:10:43.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,代数  算法  炼金术  酒精 这些英语单词中的 al
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.95,0:10:45.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也是佐证
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.68,0:10:50.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当时阿拉伯语是科学界的通用语
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.06,0:10:54.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}11世纪时  海桑准备尝试
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.83,0:10:58.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}验证他关于光和我们如何看见的理论
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.90,0:11:02.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们设计了一套实验测定光线如何移动
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.17,0:11:04.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们在烈日下支起一顶帐篷
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.57,0:11:07.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,将它完全密封 只允许一束光穿过
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.71,0:11:10.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,射入内部的黑暗中
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.48,0:11:12.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他用他的智慧
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.81,0:11:15.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,加上一件笔直的木质工具  尺子
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.08,0:11:16.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,,海桑完成了一次科学历史上
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.98,0:11:18.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,伟大的跨越
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.55,0:11:22.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他发现光线呈直线运动
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.73,0:11:29.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这只是开始
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.73,0:11:33.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,海桑总结出成像的关键
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.16,0:11:36.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不论 眼睛还是照相机暗箱
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.23,0:11:38.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,都是通过控制光线进入
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.94,0:11:40.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,黑暗内室的小孔
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.84,0:11:43.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,光圈将我们周遭繁杂无关的
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.74,0:11:46.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,光线排除在外
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.44,0:11:48.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,光圈越小
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.11,0:11:50.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,进入的光线角度范围越小
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.68,0:11:52.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,使图像更清晰
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.88,0:11:55.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,从而不至于让光线致盲
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.69,0:11:58.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们可以分辨光线呈现的图像
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.89,0:12:02.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}海桑亲自做出了他的暗箱
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.23,0:12:04.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}令哈里发们赞叹不已
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.30,0:12:07.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}有效的暗箱需要明亮的光线
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.40,0:12:11.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}夜空中的星光对它来说太暗淡了
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.24,0:12:14.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们需要更大的孔来收集光线
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.57,0:12:17.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}同时我们需要保持焦点
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.04,0:12:19.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}望远镜从视野的
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.71,0:12:22.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}各个角度收集光线
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.05,0:12:25.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}遍布整个镜片或者镜子
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.05,0:12:28.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}开孔要比照相机暗箱的小孔大许多
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.79,0:12:32.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这是最早的望远镜之一
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.72,0:12:36.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}伽利略在1609年使用过的那个
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.83,0:12:41.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他用这个掀开了黑夜的厚重幕布
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.10,0:12:44.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}并且开始发现宇宙
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.61,0:12:58.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}都归功于镜片
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.65,0:13:01.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}镜片为望远镜提供了比我们眼睛
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.75,0:13:04.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}更大的光线收集区域
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.09,0:13:07.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}大桶比小桶可以收集更多的雨水
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.53,0:13:10.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}现代的望远镜拥有更大收集区域
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.46,0:13:12.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}高度敏感的探测器
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.16,0:13:15.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}并可以长时间锁定同一目标
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.10,0:13:18.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}以搜集尽可能多的光线
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.47,0:13:21.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}像哈勃 这样的太空望远镜
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.27,0:13:23.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}搜集来自最久远星系的
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.14,0:13:24.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}光线
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.81,0:13:27.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}为我们带来大量的更清晰的宇宙图片
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.61,0:13:33.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,海桑发现了光线成像的原理
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.35,0:13:35.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但这并不是他最最伟大的成就
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.72,0:13:38.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他是有史以来设定
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.46,0:13:41.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,科学原则的第一人
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.16,0:13:43.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他创造了一套纠错机制
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.70,0:13:46.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一套系统的 严格的
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.20,0:13:48.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,审查错误观念的机制
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.87,0:13:53.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,探究真相是困难的
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.87,0:13:56.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,探究真相的道路是崎岖的
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.88,0:13:59.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,作为追寻真相的人
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.18,0:14:02.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不轻易下判断 不轻信古人所云
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.31,0:14:05.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是十分明智的
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.22,0:14:09.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你必须质疑并且谨慎的验证这些理论
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.05,0:14:11.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,从各个角度
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.59,0:14:14.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你只能接受论据和实验的结果
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.86,0:14:18.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而不是别人的说法
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.26,0:14:20.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为每个人都有弱点
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.83,0:14:23.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,没有人是完美的
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.54,0:14:25.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,作为寻求真相的人
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.00,0:14:28.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们必须怀疑并质疑
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.37,0:14:31.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们自己的理论  反复论证
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.01,0:14:36.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,避免陷入偏见与疏忽
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.95,0:14:42.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,接受这些方针  真相就在眼前
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.07,0:15:02.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这就是科学的方式
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.27,0:15:05.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}得益于此 我们的机器人大使可以
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.11,0:15:08.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}航行到太阳系的边缘乃至无限的宇宙
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.28,0:15:12.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}它扩展了我们的生命长度
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.62,0:15:14.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}将过去的失落世界
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.42,0:15:16.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,带回现在
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.82,0:15:20.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,科学使我们可以对遥远的未来
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.09,0:15:22.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,做出预测
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.59,0:15:26.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,让我们可以彼此以光速交流
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.10,0:15:28.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就像你我之间  此时此刻
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.73,0:15:30.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这种思考的方式带给我们力量
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.80,0:15:34.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那种海桑都认为神奇的力量
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.94,0:15:42.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他将我们带上这条崎岖 无尽的道路
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.18,0:15:47.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,将我们带到一个地方
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.09,0:15:51.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在那里即使光线也被黑暗掩盖
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.09,0:16:02.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,光线有着独一无二的属性
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.26,0:16:04.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,以人类存在的领域来说
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.16,0:16:06.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,比如光的速度
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.33,0:16:08.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,光的基础微粒  光子
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.46,0:16:11.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当它从原子或分子中诞生时
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.17,0:16:13.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就有光的速度
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.97,0:16:16.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也只有这一种速度
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.14,0:16:18.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们尚未发现其他任何可以立即
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.98,0:16:21.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,从0加速到速度极限的现象
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.95,0:16:24.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,没有别的东西可以移动这么快
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.18,0:16:26.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当我们尝试将其他粒子不断加速
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.85,0:16:29.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,越接近光速  阻力越大
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.59,0:16:31.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并且越来越重
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.35,0:16:32.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还没有任何实验可以
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.82,0:16:36.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,将粒子加速到光的速度
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.50,0:16:46.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,哪是什么
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.17,0:16:48.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你听了吗
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.37,0:16:50.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,,说到哪了 哦 对了
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.54,0:16:54.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,没有什么东西能表现的像光那样
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.64,0:16:58.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我无法将它的这些奇怪的性质
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.11,0:17:00.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,与我感知的其他事物协调一致
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.78,0:17:03.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们本能地更加信任我们的感官
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.79,0:17:05.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而不愿接受我们的测量仪器
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.89,0:17:07.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所告诉我们的现实的确切本质
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.82,0:17:09.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,对于以普通速度运动的普通大小的物体
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.03,0:17:11.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们的感官没有问题
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.86,0:17:16.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是却不适用于光速那些神奇的规则
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.64,0:17:24.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们甚至不明白为什么会有宇宙速度极限
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.04,0:17:27.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,时间在达到光速时静止
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.51,0:17:29.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,到底什么是光
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.52,0:17:37.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}艾萨克·牛顿始终对光非常着迷
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.05,0:17:39.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}从他还是个孩子时
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.66,0:17:44.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}就在这个房子里
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.17,0:17:53.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他在弱冠之年  就是第一位
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.37,0:17:56.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,破译彩虹奥秘的人
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.24,0:18:03.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}牛顿发现有些光  白光
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.58,0:18:06.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}由所有彩虹的颜色混合而成
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.09,0:18:11.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}重大的发现
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.19,0:18:13.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他将之称为 光谱
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.76,0:18:18.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}来源于拉丁语中的幻影 或者幽灵
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.27,0:18:32.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,牛大师 抱歉打扰了
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.28,0:18:34.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,晚饭再不吃就要坏了
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.88,0:18:40.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}哎呀不 艾萨克 别把放大镜放下
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.08,0:18:43.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}光里还有更神奇的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.89,0:18:46.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}密码  通向宇宙的钥匙
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.16,0:18:57.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,牛顿错过了一项很重要的发现
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.10,0:19:00.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他错过了那扇通向神秘宇宙的门
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.24,0:19:04.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那扇门直到150年后才再次开启
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.31,0:19:06.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,归功于另一位科学家
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.64,0:19:08.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,1800年 在工作时
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.34,0:19:10.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,无意间发现了一些证据
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.35,0:19:13.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一个肉眼看不见的世界就在我们周围
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.92,0:19:19.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,晚上  威廉·赫歇尔搜索天空
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.39,0:19:21.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,使用当时最大的望远镜
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.89,0:19:24.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,白天  赫歇尔做实验
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.86,0:19:27.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,根据牛顿的研究结果  已知日光
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.53,0:19:29.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,由不同颜色的光混合而成
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.93,0:19:32.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所有人都知道  在户外
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.33,0:19:34.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,日光带来热量
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.07,0:19:38.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}威廉赫歇尔不禁疑问
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.11,0:19:40.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}哪种颜色的光带着更多的热量
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.71,0:19:44.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}科学天才的天性就是对那些
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.85,0:19:47.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们认为理所当然的事情产生疑问
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.68,0:19:50.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}然后做用实验证实
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.29,0:19:55.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}赫歇尔放在光照范围之外的温度计
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.76,0:19:57.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}是他的对照物
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.46,0:20:01.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}对照物在实验中
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.39,0:20:04.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}不参加实验操作
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.06,0:20:06.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这样才能知道你的实验物
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.20,0:20:08.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}是否真的是对实验本身产生反应
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.43,0:20:10.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在赫歇尔的试验中
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.77,0:20:12.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}验证的是
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.40,0:20:13.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}颜色和温度的关系
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.81,0:20:16.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他用一个温度计做对照
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.91,0:20:18.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}放在白纸上
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.61,0:20:21.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}日光照射之外
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.25,0:20:25.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}那个声音又来了
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.82,0:20:28.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}到底是什么
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.29,0:20:36.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}红光比蓝光产生更多的热
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.83,0:20:41.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}有趣的发现 但还不算惊天动地
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.42,0:21:07.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}你的温度计没有问题
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.16,0:21:10.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}你只是发现了一种新的光
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.37,0:21:22.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,赫歇尔是首位发现在光谱中
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.47,0:21:25.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,红色以外（以下）不可见光的人
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.71,0:21:28.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就是红外线名字的由来（infra red）
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.64,0:21:30.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,英语的infra在拉丁语中意为 之下
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.84,0:21:32.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它不可见
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.45,0:21:34.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们的眼睛对这类光不敏感
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.85,0:21:37.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们的皮肤不同  我们可以感受到热
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.75,0:21:39.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这才是真正的重大发现
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.59,0:21:41.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是光线之中依然隐藏着
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.02,0:21:44.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,更大的秘密
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.38,0:21:52.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}几乎与威廉赫歇尔在英格兰
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.45,0:21:55.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}发现红外线的同时
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.38,0:21:57.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}一位名叫约瑟夫·夫琅和费的孩子
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.89,0:22:00.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}从事着乏味的繁重的工作
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.39,0:22:03.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他站在盛满有毒化学物的熔炉旁
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.36,0:22:05.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}不断地搅拌
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.63,0:22:10.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}约瑟夫11岁时成了孤儿
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.46,0:22:14.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}被送给苛刻的维塞伯格
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.30,0:22:17.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他替皇家做镜子
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.27,0:22:19.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他不让约瑟夫去上学
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.57,0:22:22.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}而是白天让约瑟夫在玻璃作坊做苦力
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.81,0:22:24.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而是白天让约瑟夫在玻璃作坊做苦力
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.78,0:22:27.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}晚上去他家里做家务
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.75,0:22:34.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,快点  白痴
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.29,0:22:37.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,记住 不许读书
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.59,0:22:44.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}约瑟夫终于解脱了
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.46,0:22:48.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}维塞伯格的房子塌了
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.61,0:23:08.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}马克西米利安 巴伐利亚未来的国王
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.52,0:23:10.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}急忙来到灾难现场
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.45,0:23:11.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}向灾民伸出援手
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.02,0:23:14.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}马克西米利安出了名的关心他的臣民
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.49,0:23:16.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,马克西米利安出了名的关心他的臣民
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.12,0:23:18.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这在当年并不寻常
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.21,0:23:35.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在巴伐利亚未来国王的关怀下
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.38,0:23:36.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}年轻的约瑟夫·夫琅和费
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.01,0:23:39.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}的未来从此发生了变化
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.85,0:23:42.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}而且不仅是他个人
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.09,0:23:46.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}马克西米利亚王子资助约瑟夫
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.89,0:23:48.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}并让他的高级顾问
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.72,0:23:50.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}向这孩子提供更多的帮助
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.19,0:23:52.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}提供所需的一切
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.43,0:24:00.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}维塞伯格还在剥削他
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.17,0:24:02.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}不让他去学校
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.50,0:24:04.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}但是在王子顾问的干预下
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.57,0:24:08.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}约瑟夫进入了光学学院
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.11,0:24:13.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这小小的善举带来了非常丰厚的回报
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.59,0:24:28.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在他27岁时
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.46,0:24:30.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,约瑟夫·夫琅和费成为了首屈一指的设计师
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.73,0:24:32.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,从优质的镜片
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.77,0:24:35.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,到望远镜和其他光学器材
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.47,0:24:39.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他的工厂位于本讷迪克特伯伊昂修道院
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.37,0:24:41.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在19世纪上半叶
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.58,0:24:44.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这可是绝密的 超级的高科技
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.92,0:24:50.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,早期的本笃会修道士们
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.15,0:24:52.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,都要经过保密宣誓
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.15,0:24:54.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这种当地的风俗
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.16,0:24:55.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,加上夫琅和费实验室
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.66,0:24:57.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,严格的通行制度
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.23,0:24:59.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,让他可以持续掌控
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.23,0:25:02.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这些机密
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.40,0:25:09.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}夫琅和费在实验中使用棱镜
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.74,0:25:13.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}来寻找制作精密镜片的最佳玻璃
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.17,0:25:15.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}怎样才能更好的观察
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.91,0:25:17.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}棱镜产生的光谱呢
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.08,0:25:24.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,弗雷德里希 请把经纬仪拿来
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.92,0:25:27.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在夫琅和费安装经纬仪的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.86,0:25:29.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,经纬仪是某种望远镜
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.69,0:25:32.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我带你看看修道院的其他地方
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.63,0:25:41.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}声波听上去如此动人
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.20,0:25:47.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}想象一下 会有多迷人如果我们能看到它
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.94,0:25:51.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你想过为什么管风琴的音管长短不一吗
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.38,0:25:54.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,按下一个琴键
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.12,0:25:58.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它将一股压缩空气
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.55,0:25:59.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,送进特定的管道
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.82,0:26:01.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,产生声波
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.66,0:26:04.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果我们可以把声波速度降低几百倍
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.39,0:26:06.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它看上去就是这样的
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.23,0:26:11.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,管道的长度
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.90,0:26:13.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,决定了可以容纳何种长度的声波
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.37,0:26:14.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,决定了可以容纳何种长度的声波
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.87,0:26:16.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,短的管道发出短的声波
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.97,0:26:21.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,短的声波产生高的音调或者频率
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.22,0:26:29.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们把声波停下 仔细看看
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.26,0:26:36.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,相邻波之间的距离
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.22,0:26:37.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,称为 波长
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.03,0:26:40.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,长管道发出长的声波
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.56,0:26:42.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,低音调 或者低频率
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.48,0:27:37.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,布兰诗歌 这个中世纪作品的手稿
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.42,0:27:40.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就是在这间修道院发现的
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.79,0:27:46.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,声波无法在真空中传递
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.26,0:27:48.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们需要传播媒介
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.16,0:27:51.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,比如空气 水 岩石的分子
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.67,0:27:53.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但光不需要
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.80,0:27:55.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们可以在太空中穿行
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.00,0:27:57.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,速度很快
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.64,0:28:00.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,比声波在空气中快100万倍
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.78,0:28:02.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们看到的光的波长
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.78,0:28:05.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,比声波的要短得多
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.31,0:28:08.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,5万个光波
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.18,0:28:10.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就这么长
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.79,0:28:13.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,对了
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.36,0:28:14.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,夫琅和费
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.43,0:28:22.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,时间正好
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.80,0:28:24.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,正好赶上
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.47,0:28:26.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}就如同声音的波长
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.67,0:28:28.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}决定我们听到的音调
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.67,0:28:30.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}光的波长
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.17,0:28:32.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}决定了我们看到的颜色
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.64,0:28:35.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}棱镜是如何将颜色
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.11,0:28:37.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}从一束日光中分开的呢
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.65,0:28:41.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}当光穿过空气或太空
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.62,0:28:43.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}所有的颜色速度保持一致
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.02,0:28:48.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}但当它以一个角度照射到玻璃上时
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.82,0:28:51.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}光慢下来 并改变了方向
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.79,0:28:54.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在棱镜内
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.80,0:28:56.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}不同的颜色以不用的速度移动
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.14,0:29:02.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在玻璃中  蓝紫色
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.97,0:29:05.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}由我们看到的最短的光波产生
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.17,0:29:07.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}速度比红光还慢
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.21,0:29:09.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}红光的光波最长
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.48,0:29:13.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}速度的改变
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.92,0:29:16.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}将不同颜色分开
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.48,0:29:18.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}把它们的光波发散到
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.32,0:29:20.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}稍微不同的方向
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.92,0:29:23.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就是棱镜的原理
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.06,0:29:28.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果我等会情绪失控
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.36,0:29:31.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,都是因为约瑟夫·夫琅和费将要做的
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.20,0:29:34.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是牛顿可以做 却没有做的
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.74,0:29:36.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它将带来深远的影响
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.84,0:29:38.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,对我自身来说
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.70,0:30:03.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}你见证的是
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.77,0:30:05.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}物理学和天文学的结合
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.40,0:30:09.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我研究的这个领域的诞生
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.30,0:30:11.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}天体物理学
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.74,0:30:15.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,,记录在光线中
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.54,0:30:18.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在那些垂直的黑线中的
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.38,0:30:23.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是神秘的密码
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.39,0:30:26.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}夫琅和费看着它们 自忖道
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.22,0:30:28.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为什么
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.13,0:30:35.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}从外太空传来的密码
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.29,0:30:47.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这些黑色的竖线包含怎样的信息呢
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.63,0:30:51.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这些黑色的竖线包含怎样的信息呢
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.30,0:30:58.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,人们花费了上百年去思考
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.41,0:31:01.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,探询 调查 破译
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.26,0:31:23.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,很妙吧
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.43,0:31:24.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为什么
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.00,0:31:28.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,美丽的精细结构由许多层次组成
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.50,0:31:31.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}地球的化学成分 和它的大气层
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.67,0:31:34.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}生命的进化
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.64,0:31:38.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}独特的脉络
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.25,0:31:41.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们就在表面挑一个观察
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.35,0:31:43.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,令我们惊叹的大自然的颜色
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.78,0:31:46.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}到底是什么
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.92,0:31:48.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这些红色  蓝色
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.82,0:31:51.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}简直就是大自然的神奇调色盘
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.80,0:31:58.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,怎么产生的
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.10,0:32:03.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,太阳发出不同长度的光波
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.30,0:32:04.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,射到地球
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.11,0:32:08.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这些花的花瓣
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.18,0:32:09.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,吸收所有低能量的
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.78,0:32:12.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,长的红色光波
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.05,0:32:13.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是花瓣反射
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.78,0:32:17.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,短的 高能量的 蓝色光波
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.12,0:32:19.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,星光与花瓣
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.89,0:32:21.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,与水 或与梵高的互动
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.89,0:32:23.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,产生了 蓝色
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.49,0:32:25.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,最长的光波
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.66,0:32:27.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们所看到的红色
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.50,0:32:30.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有着最低的能量
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.00,0:32:35.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,颜色是我们的眼睛
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.37,0:32:37.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,分辨光波能量的方式
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.07,0:32:40.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}日落
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.81,0:32:42.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}旗帜
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.98,0:32:45.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}情人的眼睛
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.41,0:32:47.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}闪亮的新车
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.18,0:32:49.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们带来的灵感
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.18,0:32:50.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,激发你内在的某些东西
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.02,0:32:53.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,由一种特殊的变化产生
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.52,0:32:56.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,光波的能量与频率的变化
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.76,0:32:59.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}神秘的信息
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.93,0:33:01.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}那些黑色竖线
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.66,0:33:03.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}夫琅和费在光谱中看到的
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.70,0:33:05.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}它们怎么产生的
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.83,0:33:08.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}它们产生于 某些特定颜色
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.04,0:33:10.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}的光波被吸收时
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.84,0:33:13.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}那是发生在另一个层面的事情
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.41,0:33:16.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}比我们身处的这个世界小的多得多
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.44,0:33:19.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}要去那里 我们必须变得
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.05,0:33:21.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}比现在小100亿倍
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.55,0:33:26.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们可以从这些原子中任选一个
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.95,0:33:30.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}还是选氢原子吧
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.06,0:33:32.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,氢原子是宇宙中
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.56,0:33:34.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,最普遍的一种
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.96,0:33:37.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,最简单的
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.87,0:33:48.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}只有一个电子
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.08,0:33:50.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}只有一个质子
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.61,0:33:52.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们进入了量子领域
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.71,0:33:54.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这并不符合
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.55,0:33:57.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}通常的经验
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.32,0:34:00.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}常识在这里不起作用
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.56,0:34:03.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}以氢原子的电子为例
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.49,0:34:07.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在原子中 电子
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.76,0:34:09.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}不存在于轨道之间
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.50,0:34:11.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}它从一个轨道消失
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.30,0:34:13.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}又在另一个轨道出现
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.97,0:34:15.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}就像你坐电梯从2楼去4楼
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.80,0:34:19.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}却凭空消失
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.11,0:34:20.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}还有
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.84,0:34:23.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}量子电梯并不会停在特定的楼层
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.81,0:34:27.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}电子的轨道尺寸有着严格的限制
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.25,0:34:30.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}每种元素的原子都不相同
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.62,0:34:33.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这就是元素各不相同的原因
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.99,0:34:36.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}所有物质的化学属性都由它的电子的轨道决定
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.96,0:34:39.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}将电子束缚在轨道上的力量
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.86,0:34:41.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}和重力没有丝毫关系
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.70,0:34:45.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}它是电气引力
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.27,0:34:47.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}电子沿着波浪形的圆环
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.60,0:34:49.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}环绕氢原子的原子核运行
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.87,0:34:52.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}从一个轨道跳到另一个轨道
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.67,0:34:53.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}忽上忽下
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.98,0:34:55.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}轨道越大
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.38,0:34:57.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}电子的能量越大
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.45,0:35:01.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}电子必须获取能量才能跳跃到更大的轨道上
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.02,0:35:04.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}然后必须释放能量才能跳回来
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.85,0:35:11.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}每次向上的跳跃都是原子吸收光波的结果
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.63,0:35:15.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们还不知道是什么使它向下跳跃
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.46,0:35:19.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们只知道向下跳跃产生光波
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.07,0:35:23.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这种光波的颜色与轨道间的能量差异相吻合
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.41,0:35:32.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}太阳的表面辐射出所有颜色的光波
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.85,0:35:34.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}如果你透过棱镜看日光
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.68,0:35:36.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}你能看到它的光谱
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.32,0:35:42.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}当你用望远镜放大光谱时
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.19,0:35:44.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}就像约瑟夫·夫琅和费那样
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.09,0:35:45.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}你就可以窥视
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.69,0:35:48.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}电子在原子中跳跃的真相
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.93,0:35:51.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}当电子的能量衰弱
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.17,0:35:52.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}它降到较低的轨道时
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.87,0:35:55.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}光波逸散
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.27,0:35:57.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}大多数不会到我们这里
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.71,0:35:59.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这就留下了一个黑暗的空当
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.27,0:36:02.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}或者说 光谱中的黑色竖线
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.21,0:36:04.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这些黑线就是
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.78,0:36:08.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}氢原子在太阳大气层中造成的阴影
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.38,0:36:11.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}钠原子发出不同的阴影
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.12,0:36:14.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他们的电子按照不同的曲子跳舞
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.22,0:36:17.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}一粒盐由钠原子和氯原子组成
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.96,0:36:22.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}千万亿的原子疯狂地舞动
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.43,0:36:25.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}仅仅是在一粒盐中
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.30,0:36:28.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}一个铁原子有26个电子
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.24,0:36:33.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}庞大的宛如百老汇音乐剧的制作团队
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.31,0:36:40.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}当你用分光仪观察星星时
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.25,0:36:44.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在它大气层中所有元素上都能看到黑线
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.39,0:36:46.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}给我任意一个物体的光谱
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.29,0:36:49.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}不论是在地球上的 还是在遥远的星星上
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.09,0:36:52.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我都可以告诉你 它的元素构成
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.16,0:36:55.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,夫琅和费线是元素的原子签名
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.80,0:36:59.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,遍布整个宇宙
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.80,0:37:01.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如同科学历史上的
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.90,0:37:04.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,其他重大发现一样  它带来了
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.44,0:37:07.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,更新更深层次的谜团
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.44,0:37:10.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还有更多的
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.44,0:37:13.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,秘密依然藏在光线中
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.43,0:37:24.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当夫琅和费把望远镜和棱镜结合在一起
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.37,0:37:26.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,用它们探索天空
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.64,0:37:30.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他将星星与我们之间的距离缩短了
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.12,0:37:43.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他39岁时
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.85,0:37:46.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}身患重病
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.02,0:37:48.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}可能是由于早年长期曝露在
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.69,0:37:51.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}制作玻璃的有毒化学物质的缘故
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.63,0:37:55.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}你永远不知道下一个天才在何处诞生
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.57,0:38:04.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}不知道我们错过了多少天才
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.07,0:38:07.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}对一位孤儿的善行给王子
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.34,0:38:10.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}和他的王国带来不可计量的财富
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.71,0:38:13.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}夫琅和费的发现将巴伐利亚
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.15,0:38:17.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}从偏僻的乡下变成高科技的制造中心
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.25,0:38:21.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在他弥留之际  政府急切地
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.69,0:38:24.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}想要保留他所有的关于
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.59,0:38:26.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}高科技光学玻璃的宝贵知识
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.93,0:38:31.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}但这只能让一个人知道
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.87,0:38:34.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}此人有着最高级别的涉密权限
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.07,0:38:35.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}铸币局主管
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.92,0:38:55.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}政府保留了夫琅和费的技术
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.52,0:38:57.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}用于制造完美的光学玻璃
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.43,0:39:00.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}一个上百年的国家机密
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.70,0:39:03.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,后来证明这给某人带来很大的阻碍
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.73,0:39:05.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,以后我们会提到
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.23,0:39:07.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但夫琅和费不能容忍这样
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.80,0:39:10.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,对他的科学研究保密
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.40,0:39:14.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他知道科学需要开放才能昌盛
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.04,0:39:18.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们对于自然的了解属于全世界
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.11,0:39:21.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,夫琅和费发现谱线后
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.05,0:39:23.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他立即发表了所有的成果
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.62,0:39:26.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如此重要的发现带来的影响
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.45,0:39:29.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,持续至今
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.39,0:39:36.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他的谱线揭示了可观测的宇宙
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.40,0:39:39.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}是由相同的元素构成
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.70,0:39:45.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}行星们
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.31,0:39:55.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}恒星们
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.15,0:40:02.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}星系们
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.53,0:40:09.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们  还有所有的生命体
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.20,0:40:19.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}拥有共同的物质
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.18,0:40:26.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他让我们知道了
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.88,0:40:29.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}其他星球的大气层中有些什么
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.82,0:40:35.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}远在上百万光年外的星系中
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.49,0:40:38.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}谱线不止揭示了遥远物体的成分
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.52,0:40:42.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}也揭示了它们是在靠近还是远离我们
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.23,0:40:45.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}通过它 我们发现我们的宇宙还在扩张
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.33,0:40:48.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}但光谱学带给我们的最大启示可能是
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.94,0:40:51.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}发现了根本就看不见的物质
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.75,0:40:59.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}由暗物质组成的隐蔽宇宙
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.95,0:41:03.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}质量比我们熟悉的宇宙超出6倍
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.22,0:41:05.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}由某些神秘的物质组成
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.42,0:41:09.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}不会发出 反射或者吸收任何形式的光
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.02,0:41:12.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}因为它的引力我们才知道它的存在
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.53,0:41:14.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}它的引力吸引着星系
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.63,0:41:17.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}并为其中的恒星加速
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.37,0:41:24.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们的眼睛可以看见很多种类的光
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.87,0:41:28.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,认为我们的自然只有可见光
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.31,0:41:30.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就如同听的音乐
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.64,0:41:32.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只有一个八度
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.78,0:41:36.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,其实还有很多很多
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.82,0:41:38.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们仅仅是波长的区别
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.79,0:41:40.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只是范围很大
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.92,0:41:43.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,比如 红外线
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.83,0:41:51.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}威廉·赫歇尔发现的那种
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.00,0:41:53.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}X光
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.84,0:42:00.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}无线电波
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.65,0:42:07.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}伽马射线
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.29,0:42:16.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}不仅是看东西的方式不同
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.59,0:42:18.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}不同的光
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.19,0:42:21.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,揭示出宇宙中不同的物体和现象
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.83,0:42:24.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,比方说通过伽马射线 我们可以看到
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.03,0:42:26.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}遥远星系的神秘爆炸
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.80,0:42:29.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}否则就可能错过
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.04,0:42:34.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}通过微波 我们可以看到
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.94,0:42:37.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\i1}宇宙诞生之初的情景
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.88,0:42:43.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们只不过 刚刚睁开眼睛
